00:02:16.530 --> 00:02:21.050
&gt;&gt; Notice how Screen Reader pronounced
the word Udacity as Uda city.

00:02:21.050 --> 00:02:24.940
This is a pretty common occurrence
because the speech synthesizer is

00:02:24.940 --> 00:02:28.120
trying to take its best guess at
how to pronounce certain words.

00:02:28.120 --> 00:02:29.990
And of course, it makes mistakes.

00:02:29.990 --> 00:02:34.130
However, Screen Reader users are pretty
resilient to these kinds of situations

00:02:34.130 --> 00:02:39.130
because we often tend to look
at different web pages, and

00:02:39.130 --> 00:02:43.620
words aren't always spelled
the way we expect them to be.

00:02:43.620 --> 00:02:47.950
To make the long story short,
it suffices to know that Screen Readers

00:02:47.950 --> 00:02:52.840
do provide a lot of shortcut keys, and
one of those shortcut keys is a way to

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:56.680
spell a specific word or
even a sentence, letter by letter.

00:02:56.680 --> 00:03:01.250
So for example, if I did want to know
how the word Udacity is spelled,

00:03:01.250 --> 00:03:05.150
I could simply jump to the place on
the web page where the word occurs.

00:03:05.150 --> 00:03:08.665
&gt;&gt; Heading level, heading level 2,
contents, heading level 2,

00:03:08.665 --> 00:03:12.115
4 items, history, heading level 2,
form control, 1 item,

00:03:12.115 --> 00:03:17.080
headings menu, 1 item, heading level 1,
Udacity, heading level 1, Udacity.

00:03:17.080 --> 00:03:22.007
&gt;&gt; And then I can press Ctrl+Opt+W to
have voice over spell this word out

00:03:22.007 --> 00:03:22.740
for me.

00:03:22.740 --> 00:03:28.050
&gt;&gt; Udacity, uniform, delta,
Udacity, U-D-A-C-I-T-Y.

00:03:28.050 --> 00:03:31.680
&gt;&gt; So using the alternative spelling
is just going to teach me to spell

00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:32.980
things wrong.

00:03:32.980 --> 00:03:36.420
So please refrain from using
these methods in the name.

00:03:36.420 --> 00:03:39.430
It will improve the experience
of Screen Reader users.

